ons? Schedule an advising appointment with a Career Advisor by clicking the “Schedule an Advising Appointment” button below.            Career Services Available to Alumni       Service/Resource  Link(s)  Alumni Access Level       UIC Career Services Appointments    Schedule An Appointment   Alumni may schedule appointments.     UIC Career Workshops (on campus)    Current Programs and Events  Workshop Decscriptions   Alumni have lifetime access to attend any advertised workshops on campus.     UIC Career Fairs    Current Programs and Events  Career Fair Descriptions   Alumni have lifetime access to attend all UIC-sponsored career fairs unless noted otherwise.     Access to UICcareers.com (UIC's job board)    UICcareers.com   Click the "Get Access to UICcareers.com" button  if you need help setting up or re-activating your UICcareers.com account.          Get Access to UICcareers.com       Additional Resources     Coaching/Advising/Counseling Resources         Coaching    National Career Development Association’s career counselor directory – Identify one-on-one career assistance in your area.  UIC Career Services – Schedule a one-to-one advising appointment with a career advisor after graduation.  UIC Office of Applied Psychological Services (OAPS)* – Obtain professional assistance with stress, anxiety or depression.  Fees are on a sliding scale.   *This mental health clinic is part of the Psychology Department at UIC. OAPS serves the UIC community, including faculty, staff, and students, as well as those living or working in the greater Chicago area. OAPS offers therapy for adults, children, families, and couples – helping individuals make changes that will improve their relationships and personal functioning, and enhance their ability to deal with various life stressors, including career transition.        Network with Other Alumni         network    UIC Alumni Website  UIC Alumni & Friends LinkedIn Group (Note:  LinkedIn login required)         College-Specific Alumni Resources         collegeresources    College of Engineering Career Center offers alumni access to career fairs, resume and cover letter review, LinkedIn profile assessment and mock interviews. You are encouraged to visit the Engineering Alumni Association .  Liberal Arts and Science Alumni Association offers mentoring opportunities for alumni.  College of Nursing hosts a job board to help alumni locate potential opportunities. Alumni are also encouraged to check UICcareers.com for opportunities.  School of Public Health Career Services meets a variety of career development needs through resources and events for alumni.   Alumni are always encouraged to check the UICcareers.com website (UIC’s job board) for full-time, part-time, and internship opportunities.             Schedule an Advising Appointment                   UIC Logo        Career Services         Students    Career Planning Guide    Make an Appointment    FAQs      Employers    Post a Position    UICcareers.com      Campus Partners    Campus Partners    Program/Workshop Request Forms        Footer Menu    Career Programs and Events    UICcareers    UIC Student Employment Office         Contact   Suite 3050 1200 West Harrison Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-2300  Fax: (312) 413-0383  careerservices@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 